Chat Completions (OpenAI protocol)

POST /chat/completions or POST /v1/chat/completions

Request and response fields are OpenAI Chat Completions compatible. Common parameters:

Field	Type	Description
model	string	Model ID—see Supported models; default tier is deepseek-v4-flash
messages	array	Array of messages (required), each with role and content
stream	boolean	Whether to stream; default false
temperature	number	temperature: sampling temperature (optional)
max_tokens	integer	max_tokens: max tokens to generate (optional)
Non-streaming response (OpenAI shape):

{
  "id": "chatcmpl-xxx",
  "object": "chat.completion",
  "choices": [{
    "index": 0,
    "message": { "role": "assistant", "content": "..." },
    "finish_reason": "stop"
  }],
  "usage": {
    "prompt_tokens": 12,
    "completion_tokens": 8,
    "total_tokens": 20
  }
}
Messages (Anthropic protocol)

POST /v1/messages (full URL with Anthropic base: https://api.nanobridge.net/anthropic/v1/messages). On the OpenAI base host you may also use POST /anthropic/v1/messages.

Requests and responses follow the Anthropic Messages API. The gateway translates to Chat Completions upstream while staying Anthropic-compatible on the wire.

Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>, or X-Api-Key: <API_KEY> (same as OpenAI).

Field	Type	Description
model	string	Model ID—see Supported models; default tier is deepseek-v4-flash
messages	array	messages (required); system may be a separate field or inside messages
max_tokens	integer	max_tokens: max reply length (usually required by Anthropic clients)
stream	boolean	Whether to stream; default false
With stream: true, the response is Anthropic-style text/event-stream (SSE).

curl https://api.nanobridge.net/anthropic/v1/messages \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_API_KEY>" \
  -d '{
        "model": "deepseek-v4-flash",
        "max_tokens": 1024,
        "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello!"}]
      }'
